The paper proposes a method for modeling and learning turn-taking behaviors for accessing a shared resource, which involves multi-agent interaction and learning. Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses weighted finite state transducers (WFSTs) and logistic regression classifier, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the tower-building environment, which involves human-computer interaction, indicating that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing and modeling behavior patterns, which are relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
